🚀 LAMP Stack Deployment Commands (Amazon Linux 2023 + Amazon RDS MariaDB)

➡️ sudo -s
Switch to the root user.

➡️ sudo dnf install -y mariadb1011-server
Install the MariaDB 10.11 server package.

➡️ sudo dnf install -y mariadb1011
Install the MariaDB 10.11 client package.

➡️ sudo systemctl enable mariadb
Enable the MariaDB service at system startup.

➡️ sudo systemctl start mariadb
Start the MariaDB service.

➡️ mariadb --version
Verify the installed MariaDB version.

➡️ export MariaDB_Host=marinadbinstance.cf8imwasihtm.ap-south-1.rds.amazonaws.com
Store the Amazon RDS endpoint in an environment variable.

➡️ mariadb -h marinadbinstance.cf8imwasihtm.ap-south-1.rds.amazonaws.com -P 3306 -u admin -p
Connect to the Amazon RDS MariaDB instance.

➡️ CREATE DATABASE wordpress;
Create the WordPress database.

➡️ CREATE USER 'wpuser'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'root123456';
Create a new database user.

➡️ GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON wordpress. TO 'wpuser'@'%';*
Grant all privileges on the WordPress database.

➡️ FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
Reload the privilege tables.

➡️ SHOW DATABASES;
Display all available databases.

➡️ USE wordpress;
Select the WordPress database.

➡️ SHOW TABLES;
Display all tables in the selected database.

➡️ SHOW GRANTS FOR 'wpuser'@'%';
Verify the user's permissions.

➡️ EXIT;
Exit the MariaDB shell.

🌐 Apache HTTP Server Installation

➡️ sudo dnf install -y httpd
Install the Apache HTTP Server.

➡️ sudo systemctl enable httpd
Enable Apache at system startup.

➡️ sudo systemctl start httpd
Start the Apache service.

➡️ sudo systemctl status httpd
Verify the Apache service status.

🐘 PHP Installation

➡️ sudo dnf install -y php php-cli php-fpm php-mysqlnd php-gd php-mbstring php-xml php-json php-curl php-zip wget tar unzip
Install PHP, required PHP modules, and utility packages.

➡️ sudo systemctl restart httpd
Restart Apache after installing PHP.

🌍 WordPress Installation

➡️ cd /home/ec2-user
Navigate to the EC2 user's home directory.

➡️ wget https://wordpress.org/latest.tar.gz
Download the latest WordPress package.

➡️ tar -xzf latest.tar.gz
Extract the downloaded archive.

➡️ ls
List files and directories.

➡️ cd wordpress
Navigate to the WordPress directory.

➡️ cp wp-config-sample.php wp-config.php
Create the WordPress configuration file.

➡️ cat wp-config.php
View the configuration file.

➡️ vi wp-config.php
Edit the WordPress configuration file.

📂 Deploy WordPress

➡️ cd /home/ec2-user
Return to the home directory.

➡️ sudo cp -r wordpress/ /var/www/html/*
Copy WordPress files to the Apache web root.

➡️ cd /var/www/html/
Navigate to the Apache web root.

➡️ sudo chown -R apache /var/www/html
Assign ownership of website files to Apache.

➡️ sudo chmod -R 755 /var/www/html
Set secure file and directory permissions.

➡️ sudo systemctl restart httpd
Restart Apache to apply all configuration changes.

✅ Launch WordPress

➡️ http://<EC2-Public-IP>
Open the EC2 Public IP address in a web browser to complete the WordPress installation.
